`f5bigip.TrafficSelector` Manage IPSec Traffic Selectors on BIG-IP

Resources should be named with their "full path". The full path is the combination of the partition + name (example: /Common/test-selector)


{{% examples %}}

## Example Usage

{{< chooser language "typescript,python,go,csharp" / >}}





{{< example csharp >}}

```csharp
using Pulumi;
using F5BigIP = Pulumi.F5BigIP;

class MyStack : Stack
{
    public MyStack()
    {
        var test_selector = new F5BigIP.TrafficSelector("test-selector", new F5BigIP.TrafficSelectorArgs
        {
            DestinationAddress = "3.10.11.2/32",
            Name = "/Common/test-selector",
            SourceAddress = "2.10.11.12/32",
        });
    }

}
```


{{< /example >}}


{{< example go >}}

```go

import (
	"github.com/pulumi/pulumi-f5bigip/sdk/v3/go/f5bigip"

func main() {
	pulumi.Run(func(ctx *pulumi.Context) error {
		_, err := f5bigip.NewTrafficSelector(ctx, "test_selector", &f5bigip.TrafficSelectorArgs{
			DestinationAddress: pulumi.String("3.10.11.2/32"),
			Name:               pulumi.String("/Common/test-selector"),
			SourceAddress:      pulumi.String("2.10.11.12/32"),
		})
		if err != nil {
			return err
		}
		return nil
	})
}
```

    <dd>{{% md %}}Specifies the IPsec policy that tells the BIG-IP system how to handle the packets.When creating a new traffic selector, if this parameter is not specified, the default is `default-ipsec-policy`.

            title="Optional">

    </dt>
    <dd>{{% md %}}Specifies the order in which traffic is matched, if traffic can be matched to multiple traffic selectors.Traffic is matched to the traffic selector with the highest priority (lowest order number).
When creating a new traffic selector, if this parameter is not specified, the default is `last`
{{% /md %}}</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">

When creating a new traffic selector, if this parameter is not specified, the default is `last`
{{% /md %}}</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="state_sourceaddress_go">

</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>{{% md %}}Specifies the host or network IP address from which the application traffic originates.When creating a new traffic selector, this parameter is required.
{{% /md %}}</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="state_sourceport_go">
<a href="#state_sourceport_go" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Source<wbr>Port</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">int</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>{{% md %}}Specifies the IP port used by the application. The default value is `All Ports (0)`.
{{% /md %}}</dd></dl>
